102.8	I_Love_Bees	I Love Bees	I Love Bees (also known as ilovebees or ILB for short) was an alternate reality game (ARG) that served as both a real-world experience and viral marketing campaign for the release of developer Bungie's 2004 video game Halo 2. The game was created and developed by 42 Entertainment. Many of the same personnel had previously created an ARG for the film A.I. titled The Beast. I Love Bees was commissioned by Microsoft, Halo 2's publisher.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/57/ILoveBees-Homepage.jpg/220px-ILoveBees-Homepage.jpg
